Description: CVE-2025-61145 - Fix double-free and memory leak in tiffcrop
 The tiffcrop utility has a double-free vulnerability when read_buff and
 crop_buff point to the same allocation, as both are freed unconditionally
 in the cleanup path. Additionally, five error-handling paths in
 readContigTilesIntoBuffer() leak the tilebuf allocation by returning
 without freeing it first. The default case for unsupported bit depths
 also leaks tilebuf.
 .
 This patch adds _TIFFfree(tilebuf) calls before each early return in
 readContigTilesIntoBuffer() error paths and adds a pointer comparison
 guard (read_buff != crop_buff) before freeing read_buff in the cleanup.
